The paper deals with network analysis applications, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of graph theory and optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). However, since the focus of the paper is on finding cohesive subgraphs in large labeled networks, the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) are the most likely ones. The sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) are also likely since the paper involves the design of an index structure and the use of optimization techniques, respectively.
